"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-shericka-jackson-olympics-200m-paris-2024-b2590887.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  The two-time 200m world champion will not compete at Paris 2024 after also pulling out of the 100m earlier in the week  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 269, \"end\": 279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5152010247794092e-17, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Shericka Jacksonhas pulled out ofthe women's 200mdue to injury.\", \"from\": 442, \"to\": 529, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Jamaican, a two-time world champion at 200m, withdrew from the 100m earlier in the week, but maintained she would be fit in time to compete at her preferred distance.\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 701, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 535, \"end\": 543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9999657073369875, \"rank\": 3.4293802193692975e-05, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The news follows compatriotShelly-Ann Fraser-Pryce's withdrawal from the 100m semi-final on Saturday, following a strange disagreement over a \\\"rule change\\\" entering a warm-up track in the hours before.\", \"from\": 703, \"to\": 904, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jackson, Fraser-Pryce and Elaine Thompson-Herah were part of the Jamaican trio who swept the podium for the 100m at Tokyo 2020.\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 1033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 906, \"end\": 913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\", \"score\": 0.9949911640172614, \"rank\": 0.005014958230503645, \"text\": \"Jackson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\"}, {\"begin\": 932, \"end\": 953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elaine_Thompson-Herah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elaine Thompson-Herah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elaine_Thompson-Herah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elaine_Thompson-Herah\"}, {\"begin\": 971, \"end\": 979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9999657073369875, \"rank\": 3.4293802193692975e-05, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}, {\"begin\": 1022, \"end\": 1027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8764516254387362, \"rank\": 0.14096405876720378, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thompson-Herah, the five-time Olympic champion and gold medalist over 100m and 200m in Tokyo, withdrew last month with an Achilles problem.\", \"from\": 1035, \"to\": 1174, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1122, \"end\": 1127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8764516254387362, \"rank\": 0.14096405876720378, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1157, \"end\": 1165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\", \"score\": 0.9999994107658412, \"rank\": 5.892345867817298e-07, \"text\": \"Achilles\", \"types\": [\"Q4936952\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Achilles_tendon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jamaica's hopes of a 200m medal now rest with Niesha Burgher and Lanae-Tava Thomas.\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1259, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1176, \"end\": 1183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999996463471404, \"rank\": 3.536476556347849e-07, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 1229, \"end\": 1236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bourgeoisie\", \"score\": 0.9986514131276855, \"rank\": 0.0012220392326897811, \"text\": \"Burgher\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bourgeoisie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bourgeoisie\"}, {\"begin\": 1252, \"end\": 1258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"score\": 0.8761136586259043, \"rank\": 0.14137019871898476, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jackson last raced on 9 July at the Gyulai Istvan Memorial in Szekesfehervar, Hungary, but pulled up on the home stretch of the 200m, prompting her to not double at Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1437, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1261, \"end\": 1268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\", \"score\": 0.9949911640172614, \"rank\": 0.005014958230503645, \"text\": \"Jackson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\"}, {\"begin\": 1323, \"end\": 1337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sz\\u00e9kesfeh\\u00e9rv\\u00e1r\", \"score\": 0.9990568681734503, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Szekesfehervar\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sz\\u00e9kesfeh\\u00e9rv\\u00e1r\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sz\\u00e9kesfeh\\u00e9rv\\u00e1r\"}, {\"begin\": 1339, \"end\": 1346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.9998791416856265, \"rank\": 0.00012086680517076627, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}, {\"begin\": 1426, \"end\": 1436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5152010247794092e-17, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That decision was based on coach and I,\\\" Jackson said this week.\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1504, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1481, \"end\": 1488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\", \"score\": 0.9949911640172614, \"rank\": 0.005014958230503645, \"text\": \"Jackson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a combination of a lot of stuff.\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1543, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I made that decision not to contest the 100m\\u2026 and focus only on the 200, and I think we are pretty happy with that.\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1663, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I just [want] to compete at my best, as everybody is here to win.\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1729, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The focus is on the individual event first and then we speak about the relay after\\u2026\\\"  The absence of Jackson, who holds a national record of 21.41secs, opens up the event with the Saint Lucia's 100m gold medalist Julien Alfred and the USA's Gabby Thomas no the favourites, with Team GB's hopes resting with Daryl Neita, Dina Asher-Smith and Bianca Williams.\", \"from\": 1731, \"to\": 2089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1833, \"end\": 1840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\", \"score\": 0.9949911640172614, \"rank\": 0.005014958230503645, \"text\": \"Jackson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Jackson\"}, {\"begin\": 1967, \"end\": 1970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.743489082921939, \"rank\": 0.33223113035315016, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1973, \"end\": 1985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 2.0040096867179484e-13, \"text\": \"Gabby Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\"}, {\"begin\": 2010, \"end\": 2017, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999999870397, \"rank\": 1.2781700301148296e-11, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2052, \"end\": 2068, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dina Asher-Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\"}, {\"begin\": 2073, \"end\": 2088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bianca_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bianca Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bianca_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bianca_Williams\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Jamaican's late withdrawal was noticed by her fellow competitors in the call room, including Neita, who ran 22.39secs, finishing just 0.19secs off the fastest qualifier Gabby Thomas.\", \"from\": 2091, \"to\": 2277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2095, \"end\": 2103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9999657073369875, \"rank\": 3.4293802193692975e-05, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I saw she wasn't in the call room and I guess it's the championships and anything can happen at the last moment,\\\" Neita said.\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2405, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I really need to stay focused on myself, I can not really be looking at the field too much but I just wish her the best with whatever's happening.\\\"\", \"from\": 2407, \"to\": 2555, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fraser-Pryce revealed her disappointment at her Games ending on Saturday night, stating: \\\"It is difficult for me to find the words to describe the depth of my disappointment.\", \"from\": 2557, \"to\": 2731, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I know that my supporters share and shoulder this disappointment with me.\", \"from\": 2733, \"to\": 2807, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am truly blessed to have had the steadfast support of my fans since my Olympic debut in 2008.\", \"from\": 2808, \"to\": 2903, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The support of my fans, my country, and the larger community has rooted me in immense gratitude that has sustained me throughout my career.\", \"from\": 2905, \"to\": 3045, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With every step and win, you all have been there for me.\", \"from\": 3047, \"to\": 3104, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My faith has always affirmed my trust in my journey.\", \"from\": 3105, \"to\": 3157, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thank you for continuing to be with me today and every day.\\\"\", \"from\": 3158, \"to\": 3218, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 3220, \"to\": 3450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3271, \"end\": 3282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.1952525090353667e-12, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"